in’s dictatorship in the wake of World War II, focusing on bribery as an enduring and important presence in many areas of Soviet life. Based on extensive research in recently declassified Soviet archives, The Art of the Bribe offers revealing insights into the Soviet state, its system of law and repression, and everyday life during the years of postwar Stalinism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBriberyzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aBriberyzSoviet Union. 0aCorruptionzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aPolitical corruptionzSoviet Union. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030017525740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224764423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300224764/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles